sub_title: Health Economist at The Defeat-NCD Partnership
summary: A Myanmar Physician and Public Health Specialist who has recently finished her PhD program of "The Burden of Health Care Use and the Feasibility of Health Insurance Reform in Myanmar". She is a freelance consultant for UN organizations and INGOs in Thailand and Myanmar since Jan 2014. Previously she joined as a researcher at the Health Intervention and Technology Assessment Program (HITAP), Thailand for 3 years. Before this, she served 7 years of extensive medical and public health care provision including nutrition and Maternal and Child Health care (MCH) as a Medical Officer, the Ministry of Health and Sport, Myanmar.
